# Cursor Configuration Authoring

Rules for editing Cursor config files. Inherits from `always.md` and `etiquette.md`.

## File Types

| Folder | Extension | Purpose |
|--------|-----------|---------|
| `rules/` | `.mdc` (auto-loaded), `.md` (reference) | Behavior rules |
| `commands/` | `.md` | User-triggered workflows |
| `agents/` | `.mdc` | Agent personas |

## Rule Format (.mdc with globs)

```markdown
---
name: 'Rule Name'
description: 'One-line purpose'
globs: ["pattern1", "pattern2"]
alwaysApply: false
---

# Rule Title

Content here...
```

## Command Format

```markdown
# Command Name

You are a [role]. [One-line purpose].

## Session Scope
[What this handles / redirects]

## Workflow
[Step-by-step process]

## Related Commands
[Cross-references]
```

## Best Practices

- **Reference, don't duplicate** - Point to `always.md`, `etiquette.md`
- **Cross-reference** - Link related commands
- **Tables for quick reference** - Action/command/notes format
- **Follow-up questions** - End sections with examples

## Naming Conventions

- Lowercase with hyphens: `git/commit.md`
- Use hierarchical folders: `git/`, `session/`, `ml/`, `sync/`
- Prefix with `dir-` for directory-conditional rules

## Never Do

- Duplicate content from other rules (reference instead)
- Create commands without Session Scope
- Forget follow-up question examples
- Use `alwaysApply` or `globs` frontmatter in plain `.md` files (only `.mdc` is auto-loaded; `.md` may use `tag`/`scope` for organization)
